<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB01053</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT INSTITUTING BUDGET REFORM THAT WILL ENSURE THE EQUITABLE DISTRIBUTION OF FUNDS FOR BOTH THE NATIONAL AND LOCAL GOVERNMENT UNITS FOR THE PURPOSE OF PROMOTING VILLAGE EMPOWERMENT, ENABLING THEM TO BE AN EFFECTIVE INSTRUMENT IN ATTAINING INCLUSIVE GROWTH, APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to address existing gaps, among which is the measly sum of LGU share in the National Budget
where LGU shares, through the allocation to LGUs and IRA translates only to a mere 15% of the 
National Budget.

Proposes to institutionalize rational and equitable budget distribution for LGU development
for them to be active participants in national building.

States that the amount allocated to the LGUs will be referred to as the "Local Development Fund
(LDF), which will be divided among the different political subdivisions solely for developmental 
projects, activities and programs (PAPs) based on the approved Comprehensive Development Plans
(CDPs).

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>LOYOLA, DAHLIA A.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-02</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Savellano (000 2019-09-19)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Referred to Stakeholders on 2019-08-07</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Referred to the Department of Interior and Local Government for position paper.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON APPROPRIATIONS ON 2019-07-24</td></tr></table>